'''Mollazehi''' ({{lang-bal|'''ملازهي'''}}) is a [[Baloch people|Baloch]] tribe found in [[Hiduj]] and Northern [[Sarbaz County|Sarbaz]]. They are known as (Mollazadeh) in the [[Sarbaz County]]. They are Descendants of Mir Pordel Khan, who they claim to have migrated in the early [[19th Century]] from [[Mand (Kech District)|Mand]] in the [[Kech District]] of today's [[Balochistan, Iran.|Balochistan]] province of Iran.

==Etymology==
Mollazahi in [[Balochi language|Balochi]] means Descendants of [[Mullah|Mollas]] (Wisdom seeker.)

==Origins==
Mollazehi's of [[Hiduj]] and Northern [[Sarbaz County]] are one of the 16 clans of the [[Rind (tribe)|Rinds]].<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=42IsAAAAMAAJ|title=Göttinger geographische Abhandlungen|date=1974-01-01|publisher=Geographisches Institut der Universität.|page=38|language=de}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=jb61AAAAIAAJ|title = Baluchistan District Gazetteer Series|last = (Pakistan)|first = Baluchistan|date = 1907-01-01|publisher = printed at Bombay Education Society's Press|page = 99|language = en}}</ref> Rind clans include: [[Askani]], [[Bangizai]], [[Bugani]], [[Dagarani]], [[Gazakandi]], Gohramzai, Kahmaki, Kolagi, Miranzai, Mollazehi, Nohani, [[Perozai]], Shahalzai, Shahozai, Kiazai, [[Maheer]] and Shelo-Mir.<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":0" />

